<p>I'm working on a web application written in ASP.NET MVC 2. I'm creating templates for my views, and I'm using the <code>asp:ContentPlaceHolder</code> so that I can paste in the content into the template.</p>  <p>Here is an example of a master template:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;%@ Master Language="C#" Inherits="System.Web.Mvc.ViewMasterPage" %&gt;&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;  &lt;html lang="en"&gt;  &lt;head&gt;     &lt;meta charset="UTF-8" /&gt;     &lt;meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge, chrome=1"&gt;     &lt;meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1"&gt;     &lt;title&gt;&lt;asp:ContentPlaceHolder ID="TitleContent" runat="server" /&gt;&lt;/title&gt;     &lt;asp:ContentPlaceHolder ID="MetaContent" runat="server" /&gt;     &lt;asp:ContentPlaceHolder ID="StyleContent" runat="server" /&gt; &lt;/head&gt;  &lt;body&gt;     &lt;asp:ContentPlaceHolder ID="MainContent" runat="server" /&gt;     &lt;asp:ContentPlaceHolder ID="ScriptContent" runat="server" /&gt; &lt;/body&gt;  &lt;/html&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Now, if only <code>MainContent</code> is replace with <code>&lt;h1&gt;Hello World&lt;/h1&gt;</code> and all the other place holders are left blank, then the html output looks like this:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;  &lt;html lang="en"&gt;  &lt;head&gt;     &lt;meta charset="UTF-8" /&gt;     &lt;meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge, chrome=1"&gt;     &lt;meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1"&gt;     &lt;title&gt;Home&lt;/title&gt;   &lt;/head&gt;  &lt;body&gt;      &lt;h1&gt;Hello World&lt;/h1&gt;   &lt;/body&gt;  &lt;/html&gt; </code></pre>  <p>The browser doesn't seem to mind, but I do. I would like my output to look like this:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;  &lt;html lang="en"&gt;  &lt;head&gt;     &lt;meta charset="UTF-8" /&gt;     &lt;meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge, chrome=1"&gt;     &lt;meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1"&gt;     &lt;title&gt;Home&lt;/title&gt; &lt;/head&gt;  &lt;body&gt;     &lt;h1&gt;Hello World&lt;/h1&gt; &lt;/body&gt;  &lt;/html&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Is there a way to prevent the output of new line if the content of the place holder is left blank?</p>